    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-02-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-02-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="748"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/219.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Honduras</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Honduras</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Pursuant to the convention dated January 10,
                    1911, between the Republic of Honduras and the United States of America, I have,
                    on behalf of my Government and in accordance with its instructions, made and
                    executed with an American banking group, consisting of J. P. Morgan &amp; Co.,
                    Kuhn, Loeb &amp; Co., the National City Bank of New York, and the First National
                    Bank of New York, a loan contract, dated February 15, 1911; and with the
                    Guaranty Trust Company of New York, as fiscal agent, a contract securing the
                    said loan, dated the same day; both contracts being in the form already
                    submitted to and approved by your Department. In accordance with the
                    requirements of said contracts, I accompany an original executed counterpart of
                    each contract<note n="1" xml:id="d748fn1">Not printed.</note> in English and in
                    Spanish, to be filed with the Department of State of the United States of
                    America.</p>
                <p>Kindly acknowledge the receipt of the said contracts as executed and filed in
                    conformity to said convention.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Luis Lazo A.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
